			    STPJS 253</div>
  <p class="cont">the present distress? I would answer, &ldquo;Shall there be evil in a city and the Lord hath not done it?&rdquo;<span class="footRef">1</span></p>
  <div class="topic">Earth Now Groaning Under Corruption</div>
  <p class="std">The earth is groaning under corruption,<span class="footRef">2</span> oppression, tyranny and bloodshed; and God is coming
  out of His hiding place,<span class="footRef">3</span> as He said He would do, to vex the nations of the earth.<span class="footRef">4</span> Daniel, in his
  vision, saw convulsion upon convulsion; he &ldquo;beheld till the thrones were cast down, and the Ancient
  of Days did sit;&rdquo;<span class="footRef">5</span> and one was brought before him like unto the Son of Man; and all nations, kindred,
  tongues, and peoples, did serve and obey Him.<span class="footRef">6</span> It is for us to be righteous,<span class="footRef">7</span> that we may be wise and
  understand; for none of the wicked shall understand;<span class="footRef">8</span> but the wise shall understand,<span class="footRef">9</span> and they that
  turn many to righteousness shall shine as the stars for ever and ever.<span class="footRef">10</span></p>
  <div class="topic">It Behooves Us to Be Wise</div>
  <p class="std">As a Church and a people it behooves us to be wise,<span class="footRef">11</span> and to seek to know the will of God,<span class="footRef">12</span> and
  then be willing to do it;<span class="footRef">13</span> for &ldquo;blessed is he that heareth the word of the Lord, and keepeth it,&rdquo;<span class="footRef">14</span> say
  the Scriptures. &ldquo;Watch and pray always,&rdquo; says our Savior, &ldquo;that ye may be accounted worthy to
  escape the things that are to come on the earth, and to stand before the Son of Man.&rdquo;<span class="footRef">15</span> If Enoch,
  Abraham, Moses, and the children of Israel, and all God&rsquo;s people were saved by keeping the
  commandments of God,<span class="footRef">16</span> we, if saved at all, shall be saved upon the same principle. As God
  governed Abraham, Isaac and Jacob as families,<span class="footRef">17</span> and the children of Israel as a nation;<span class="footRef">18</span> so we, as
  a Church, must be under His guidance if we are prospered, preserved<span class="footRef">19</span> and sustained. Our only
  confidence can be in God;<span class="footRef">20</span> our only wisdom obtained from Him;<span class="footRef">21</span> and He alone must be our
  protector<span class="footRef">22</span> and safeguard,<span class="footRef">23</span> spiritually and temporally, or we fall.</p>
  <p class="std">We have been chastened by the hand of God heretofore for not obeying His commands,<span class="footRef">24</span>
  although we never violated any human law, or transgressed any human precept; yet we have treated
  lightly His commands,<span class="footRef">25</span> and departed from His ordinances,<span class="footRef">26</span> and the Lord has chastened us sore,<span class="footRef">27</span>
  and we have felt His arm and kissed the rod; let us be wise in time<span class="footRef">28</span> to come and ever remember that
  &ldquo;to obey is better than sacrifice, and to hearken than the fat of rams.&rdquo;<span class="footRef">29</span> The Lord has told us to</p>
